# i18n Translation Standard

**All user-visible strings must use translation.** Never use `text`, `placeholder`, `label`, or other string props for content shown to users. Always use the `*Tx` variant when a component offers one.

## Setup
- i18n: `@/i18n` (i18n/i18n.ts). Keys use `TxKeyPath` (e.g., `common:ok`, `loginScreen:logIn`).
- Base: `Text`, `Button` expose `tx` — use `tx`, not `text`.
- Components may expose other `*Tx` props — **always prefer those over the plain string prop**.

## Use *Tx Props on Components

When a component offers a `*Tx` prop (for strings), use it. Do not use the plain string prop.

| Component   | Use *Tx prop         | Not the string prop    |
|-------------|----------------------|-------------------------|
| TextField   | `placeholderTx`      | ~~placeholder~~         |
| TextField   | `labelTx`            | ~~label~~               |
| TextField   | `helperTx`           | ~~helper~~              |
| Toggle      | `labelTx`, `helperTx`| ~~label~~, ~~helper~~    |
| Header      | `titleTx`, `leftTx`, `rightTx` | ~~title~~, etc. |
| Card        | `headingTx`, `contentTx`, `footerTx` | ~~heading~~, etc. |
| EmptyState  | `headingTx`, `contentTx`, `buttonTx` | ~~heading~~, etc. |

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<TextField placeholderTx="loginScreen:emailFieldPlaceholder" labelTx="loginScreen:emailFieldLabel" />
<Button tx="common:ok" />
<Text tx="recipeDetailsScreen:edit" />

// ❌ BAD
<TextField placeholder="Enter email" label="Email" />
<Button text="OK!" />
```

## When Adding Text

1. **Use `tx` or the appropriate `*Tx` prop** — never the plain string version.
2. **Add key in `i18n/en.ts`** — under the right nested section (e.g., `loginScreen`, `recipeListScreen`).
3. **Add placeholders in other locales** (`fr.ts`, `ko.ts`, etc.) — same key, English string prefixed with `___` (e.g., `"___Save Recipe"`).

## Key Naming
- **camelCase** for keys.
- **Sections** per screen/feature: `loginScreen`, `recipeDetailsScreen`, `recipeListScreen`, etc.

## Example

Before:
```tsx
<TextField placeholder="Enter recipe name" label="Name" />
<Button text="Save Recipe" onPress={handleSave} />
```

After:
```tsx
<TextField placeholderTx="recipeDetailsScreen:namePlaceholder" labelTx="recipeDetailsScreen:nameLabel" />
<Button tx="recipeDetailsScreen:save" onPress={handleSave} />
```

In `i18n/en.ts`:
```ts
recipeDetailsScreen: {
  // ...existing
  namePlaceholder: "Enter recipe name",
  nameLabel: "Name",
  save: "Save Recipe",
},
```

In `i18n/fr.ts` and `i18n/ko.ts`:
```ts
recipeDetailsScreen: {
  // ...existing
  namePlaceholder: "___Enter recipe name",
  nameLabel: "___Name",
  save: "___Save Recipe",
},
```
